    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Reining In Patronage</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Flora L Ramonowski letter approves Chief Judge Judith Kaye's efforts to curtail political patronage in New York's courts (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Move to Curb Court Patronage Is Criticized'' (news article, May 17):</p>
        <p>I agree with the intentions of New York State's chief judge, Judith S. Kaye, to rein in patronage. One needs only to check the records of those receiving patronage to understand why there is such an uproar and reluctance in adhering to Judge Kaye's initiatives in curtailing political patronage in the court system.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Move to Curb Court Patronage Is Criticized'' (news article, May 17):</p>
        <p>I agree with the intentions of New York State's chief judge, Judith S. Kaye, to rein in patronage. One needs only to check the records of those receiving patronage to understand why there is such an uproar and reluctance in adhering to Judge Kaye's initiatives in curtailing political patronage in the court system.</p>
        <p>Besides, it is high time that the archaic New York State court system was merged into a more comprehensive and equitable system.  This will help eliminate some of the long ongoing patronage and inspire more fairness in distribution.</p>
        <p>FLORA L. RAMONOWSKI  New York, May 18, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a court monitor for the Fund for Modern Courts.</p>
      </block>
